WEBVTT

00:00.583 --> 00:03.417
SAM: <i>You can't assume too much</i>
<i>about anything from the outside.</i>

00:03.417 --> 00:06.625
<i>Like a house.</i>
<i>You have to get inside and explore.</i>

00:06.625 --> 00:08.125
<i>You never know what you might find.</i>

00:08.125 --> 00:11.375
Hey, Mom, I think that this might be one
of our more successful showings ever.

00:11.375 --> 00:14.709
I found ham and that mustard
that I love so much.

00:14.709 --> 00:16.208
[CHUCKLES]

00:16.792 --> 00:18.750
And as usual, I'm doing all the work.

00:19.750 --> 00:21.750
You know,
I should have just left you in the car

00:21.750 --> 00:23.583
with some water and cracked a window.

00:24.000 --> 00:26.834
I'm starving, okay?
We have been here all day.

00:26.834 --> 00:28.625
We've been here 20 minutes.

00:29.041 --> 00:33.291
I am just trying to build a business
that we can be proud of.

00:33.750 --> 00:36.458
But, you know, I'm not angry,
I'm just disappointed.

00:36.458 --> 00:39.000
Okay, I am not 5 years old.

00:39.000 --> 00:41.542
Do you really think
that that's gonna work?

00:42.500 --> 00:44.458
Because it's not gonna work.

00:46.375 --> 00:48.625
Okay, fine, I'll try harder. God.

00:49.041 --> 00:51.083
You've got mustard on your face.

00:51.083 --> 00:53.792
Ew! Go away from me.

00:55.959 --> 00:57.542
Okay.

00:59.500 --> 01:03.166
Hello, welcome. I'm Samantha.
Would you please sign in?

01:03.166 --> 01:04.542
- Lindsey.
- Hi.

01:04.959 --> 01:07.125
- We really like the house.
- Oh, good. Good.

01:07.125 --> 01:09.041
Let's see what we have here.

01:09.041 --> 01:13.083
It's nice. It's very much like one
we're interested in over in Elk Ridge.

01:13.083 --> 01:15.959
Elk Ridge? Oh, no, no, no.

01:15.959 --> 01:18.583
You do not want to live in Elk Ridge.

01:18.583 --> 01:22.083
- Why? What's wrong with Elk Ridge?
- What isn't wrong with Elk Ridge?

01:22.083 --> 01:24.917
Look, Lindsey, you seem a lot like me,

01:24.917 --> 01:29.083
and Walnut Valley
is really the place for people like us.

01:29.083 --> 01:30.417
- People like us?
- Mm-hm.

01:30.417 --> 01:32.583
You mean, because Elk Ridge
is a black neighborhood?

01:32.583 --> 01:34.792
What? Wait. It is?

01:34.792 --> 01:36.709
- As if you didn't know.
- No, I--

01:36.709 --> 01:39.083
- People like you make me sick.
- No, I don't.

01:39.083 --> 01:40.834
- Wait a minute, what did I do?
- Roger?

01:40.834 --> 01:42.875
SAM:
I don't understand what you're--

01:42.875 --> 01:44.625
This is my husband.

01:45.000 --> 01:47.250
Oh, hi. Hello.

01:47.250 --> 01:49.250
Look, I really--
I didn't know about Elk Ridge.

01:49.250 --> 01:52.959
I've never even been there, okay?
Not that I wouldn't go there, it's just that--

01:52.959 --> 01:55.166
Look,
I'm just trying to sell you a house, okay?

01:55.166 --> 02:01.083
I mean, I love black--
African American...

02:01.083 --> 02:02.208
Black people.

02:04.125 --> 02:05.333
You want a ham sandwich?

02:05.333 --> 02:07.792
Wait a minute.
Ham, that's not offensive, is it? Right?

02:07.792 --> 02:10.792
Mom! I don't even wanna be doing this.

02:19.250 --> 02:21.083
They called me a racist.

02:21.500 --> 02:25.083
I am not racist. I voted Obama.
You know, I--

02:25.083 --> 02:28.500
I watch <i>Oprah, </i>it's--
My life is full of black people.

02:28.500 --> 02:30.625
Mrs. Butterworth,
she's technically black, right?

02:31.041 --> 02:34.750
- Do you actually know any black people?
- I feel like I know Oprah.

02:35.792 --> 02:40.333
So, what, if I don't know any black people,
then I'm automatically a racist?

02:40.333 --> 02:42.458
It's not like you have any black friends,
right?

02:42.458 --> 02:46.542
Uh-- Five. No, four now.
LaShondra and I had a falling out

02:46.542 --> 02:49.000
when I didn't invite her
to my Kwanzaa party, but...

02:49.417 --> 02:52.875
Don't look at me, I'm dating Tony Dane.
Black and gay. Two birds.

02:52.875 --> 02:56.667
Wait a minute, before the accident,
did I do anything that was racist?

02:56.667 --> 02:57.875
ANDREA:
No.

02:57.875 --> 03:01.667
A black guy, a white guy and two Asians
were in the mail room one day.

03:01.667 --> 03:04.959
- Okay.
- You fired them all.

03:05.542 --> 03:08.667
Oh. I'm sorry,
I thought you were telling me a joke.

03:08.667 --> 03:11.417
Oh, Andrea, your boyfriend's on TV.

03:11.417 --> 03:14.125
Oh! Oh, turn it up, turn it up,
maybe he'll mention me.

03:14.125 --> 03:16.709
<i>Well, it looks like</i>
<i>pro basketballer Tony Dane</i>

03:16.709 --> 03:19.500
<i>is giving new meaning</i>
<i>to the term "swish."</i>

03:20.000 --> 03:21.792
<i>Caught here by paparazzi,</i>

03:21.792 --> 03:24.417
<i>the Great Dane</i>
<i>is making a full-court press</i>

03:24.417 --> 03:27.417
<i>on an unidentified male companion.</i>

03:27.417 --> 03:30.417
<i>Representatives for Dane</i>
<i>could not be reached for comment,</i>

03:30.417 --> 03:34.125
<i>but an unnamed source</i>
<i>within the organization did confirm--</i>

03:34.125 --> 03:36.291
Oh, my God. It's all over.

03:36.750 --> 03:40.208
The private jets, the parties,
the club openings.

03:40.208 --> 03:42.500
Oh, sweetie, it's gonna be okay.

03:42.500 --> 03:45.959
I'm sure you'll find another gay guy
to pretend to love you.

03:45.959 --> 03:47.959
Not like this one.

03:48.458 --> 03:50.083
- Hey.
- Miss Newly.

03:50.083 --> 03:51.750
Frank.

03:53.417 --> 03:55.667
Frank, you're black.

03:55.667 --> 03:58.834
Shh. Keep it quiet.
I'm trying to get off for Passover.

03:58.834 --> 04:00.125
No.

04:00.125 --> 04:03.834
No, I thought
I didn't have any black friends,

04:03.834 --> 04:05.583
but you're black and we're friends.

04:05.583 --> 04:07.583
- No, ma'am.
- No?

04:07.583 --> 04:10.250
Because you seem kind of black.

04:10.250 --> 04:13.417
- I mean, we are not friends.
- Of course we are.

04:13.417 --> 04:16.875
We see each other every day.
We talk. We're friends.

04:17.417 --> 04:18.750
What's my last name?

04:19.166 --> 04:20.750
Oh, uh... Brr.

04:20.750 --> 04:22.500
It's, um...

04:23.333 --> 04:26.709
Where am I from?
What's my wife's name?

04:26.709 --> 04:28.333
What's my son's name?

04:28.333 --> 04:29.959
- Marcello.
- Close.

04:29.959 --> 04:32.208
- I don't have a son.
- Fine.

04:32.208 --> 04:36.083
I'm not sure what it is you are doing,
Miss Newly, but don't.

04:36.083 --> 04:39.041
Friendships grow through time
and shared experiences.

04:39.041 --> 04:43.000
You carry my groceries,
you sign for my packages.

04:43.000 --> 04:45.250
I mean, if those aren't
shared experiences--

04:45.250 --> 04:47.583
- Good night, Miss Newly.
- Samantha.

04:47.583 --> 04:50.041
- Miss Newly.
- Frank, seriously?

04:50.041 --> 04:51.333
You don't think we're friends?

04:51.792 --> 04:54.834
Because that's just not okay with me.

04:55.041 --> 04:56.458
You know what?

04:56.458 --> 05:01.125
I'm not gonna stop
until you and I are true blue

05:01.125 --> 05:03.792
"pick me up in the middle of the night,
drive me to the airport,

05:03.792 --> 05:07.625
hold my hair back when I puke"
kind of friends.

05:08.125 --> 05:10.291
But I've already done
all those things for you.

05:10.875 --> 05:12.625
Not as friends.

05:17.041 --> 05:18.583
- Hey.
- Oh, hey.

05:18.583 --> 05:19.959
Look at that on your lip.

05:19.959 --> 05:23.417
That's a-- It's a--
Oh, shoot, what is that called? Its--

05:23.417 --> 05:25.959
It's like a mustache but not one.

05:26.875 --> 05:30.000
Joke all you want, but you don't have
a say in it, you're not my girlfriend.

05:30.000 --> 05:31.959
And apparently,
you don't plan on having one.

05:31.959 --> 05:33.875
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

05:37.041 --> 05:39.166
Hi, Frank, what's up?

05:40.208 --> 05:42.959
Hey, Todd, it's my friend, Frank.

05:42.959 --> 05:45.792
Is there any reason why you wouldn't
come down and sign for this?

05:45.792 --> 05:48.458
Because all the fun is up here.

05:48.458 --> 05:51.542
Come on, join us.
We've got food and we have fun.

05:51.542 --> 05:53.875
We got Frank. It's F day.

05:53.875 --> 05:57.417
I can think of many other words
that begin with F, but I'd get fired.

05:57.417 --> 06:00.667
"Fired." There's another F.

06:00.667 --> 06:04.041
Sam, you didn't order
my black-bean sauce again.

06:04.041 --> 06:05.458
I'm sorry.

06:05.458 --> 06:08.375
You always make sure your order's right,
but you never think of me.

06:08.375 --> 06:09.959
I always think of you.

06:09.959 --> 06:12.917
I just think of myself first.

06:12.917 --> 06:14.375
Some people find that adorable.

06:14.375 --> 06:16.250
- Well, Frank doesn't.
- He'll come around.

06:16.250 --> 06:18.792
He won't come around.
He doesn't wanna be your friend.

06:18.792 --> 06:20.834
Well, you know what?
He also didn't wanna drag out

06:20.834 --> 06:23.333
our dead Christmas tree,
but he did that.

06:23.333 --> 06:25.667
- I'll wear him down.
- Why is this your project?

06:26.125 --> 06:29.166
Because for the last two years,
I have been walking past that man

06:29.166 --> 06:32.500
and I know nothing about him.
And what does that say about me?

06:32.500 --> 06:34.917
Exactly. About you.

06:34.917 --> 06:36.333
You want more friends?

06:36.333 --> 06:38.375
Maybe think of their needs,
what they want.

06:38.792 --> 06:40.959
You know what? You're right.

06:40.959 --> 06:43.250
And what Frank wants
is to be left alone.

06:44.542 --> 06:46.166
I'm gonna bake him a pie.

06:58.834 --> 07:00.834
Oh! Oh.

07:01.125 --> 07:03.333
Oh, hi. Can you please hold this
for a second, please?

07:03.333 --> 07:05.291
- Give me the purse.
- No, I've got the purse.

07:05.291 --> 07:07.750
- Just can you hold the pie?
- Give me the purse. Hurry up.

07:07.750 --> 07:11.250
What? Oh, no. Come on, no.
No, I can't have you do this right now.

07:11.250 --> 07:12.458
When would be a good time?

07:12.458 --> 07:14.834
You don't understand
what I'm going through and I really--

07:14.834 --> 07:17.667
I cannot have you reinforcing
a racial stereotype, okay?

07:17.667 --> 07:19.041
I'm really sorry.

07:19.041 --> 07:21.375
You know,
if you can't look past the color of my skin

07:21.375 --> 07:24.750
and see me as a man stealing your purse,
I feel sorry for you.

07:24.750 --> 07:28.417
How about this? Give me your address
and then I'll send you something later.

07:28.417 --> 07:30.542
- Okay, it's 422--
- 422.

07:30.542 --> 07:32.792
- Give me the damn purse!
- What? No, I just--

07:32.792 --> 07:36.834
But there's a card in there for--
For Frank.

07:37.959 --> 07:41.166
SETH: Hello, Andrea.
- Hello, gin.

07:41.166 --> 07:43.583
Andrea, it's me. I heard about Tony.

07:44.458 --> 07:47.792
You passed on a relationship with me
to be with a gay guy.

07:47.792 --> 07:51.208
Believe me, that's the least of the reasons
I passed on you.

07:51.208 --> 07:53.667
Oh, must be rough
knowing you turned a guy gay.

07:53.667 --> 07:56.709
- I didn't turn anyone gay.
- Hey, I'm not judging, okay?

07:56.709 --> 07:58.834
In fact, I'm willing to let you
try it out on me.

07:58.834 --> 08:00.750
Tony was already gay.

08:00.750 --> 08:03.750
He asked me
to pretend to be his girlfriend.

08:03.750 --> 08:07.208
- Okay, so what was in it for you?
- What do you think?

08:07.625 --> 08:12.667
The limos, the parties,
photographs in <i>Us Weekly</i>.

08:12.667 --> 08:16.959
I was so airbrushed and pretty,
and happy.

08:17.458 --> 08:18.959
And now it's all gone.

08:18.959 --> 08:23.041
I'm meeting with his people tomorrow
so they can give me the big kiss off.

08:23.041 --> 08:25.500
I think I'm gonna miss
the airbrushing the most.

08:25.500 --> 08:27.792
Man, you are so afraid
to be with someone.

08:27.792 --> 08:30.166
- What are you talking about, afraid?
- Of being seen.

08:30.959 --> 08:36.166
By someone who sees what you need
and can really give it to you.

08:36.166 --> 08:40.917
To take you in his arms
and really, truly love you.

09:01.166 --> 09:03.667
You want your olive back?

09:03.667 --> 09:05.166
SAM:
You didn't have to call the police.

09:05.166 --> 09:07.750
I only told you that I got mugged
because I needed a ride home.

09:07.750 --> 09:11.583
I want this guy caught.
My family lives in this neighborhood.

09:11.583 --> 09:13.875
You do not live in this neighborhood.

09:13.875 --> 09:15.667
What are you doing
in this neighborhood?

09:15.667 --> 09:18.208
You're welcome for the lovely pie,
Frank.

09:18.208 --> 09:19.417
What a nice friend.

09:19.417 --> 09:22.792
I did not ask you for pie,
I did not ask you for balloons.

09:22.792 --> 09:24.875
I did not ask to be your friend.

09:24.875 --> 09:27.959
You're talking like a Dr. Seuss character.
Just a little bit.

09:27.959 --> 09:29.667
Look, why don't we both just admit

09:29.667 --> 09:31.458
- what this is all about?
- What?

09:31.458 --> 09:33.875
You're only pursuing this
so you can ease your guilt about

09:33.875 --> 09:36.041
- not having a black friend.
- No, that is not true.

09:36.041 --> 09:37.291
[SIREN WAILS]

09:37.291 --> 09:39.667
I just wanna be your friend, Frank.
Period.

09:39.667 --> 09:42.709
It's not about color.
That is everybody else's hang-up.

09:42.709 --> 09:46.083
I have no guilt. Okay?

09:46.750 --> 09:48.125
Thank you for coming, officers.

09:48.125 --> 09:50.542
- This is Miss Newly, the victim.
- Yeah.

09:50.542 --> 09:51.792
- Hello ma'am.
SAM: Hi.

09:51.792 --> 09:54.083
Can you tell us
what your attacker looked like?

09:54.083 --> 09:56.375
Yeah, he...

10:02.458 --> 10:03.834
White guy.

10:04.250 --> 10:07.667
Very white. Blindingly so.

10:07.667 --> 10:08.792
Yeah.

10:11.834 --> 10:12.959
Morning, Frank.

10:13.583 --> 10:16.041
Could you call me a cab
to my mom's house?

10:16.792 --> 10:18.000
[BLOWS WHISTLE]

10:18.000 --> 10:19.208
I'm sorry.

10:19.208 --> 10:22.208
Todd is still picking up my car
at your house

10:22.208 --> 10:23.875
and he's just taking forever.

10:24.375 --> 10:30.125
He thinks it's really funny
to change all my radio stations to gospel.

10:30.125 --> 10:31.375
[SINGING]
<i>Hallelujah</i>

10:31.375 --> 10:32.834
<i>Hal--</i>

10:32.834 --> 10:34.417
Sorry.

10:36.291 --> 10:38.041
Thank you for the pie.

10:38.458 --> 10:41.875
Oh. You're welcome. Was it good?

10:42.250 --> 10:45.500
The important thing is
you were reaching out.

10:45.500 --> 10:46.834
And I'm sorry.

10:46.834 --> 10:49.166
I've become accustomed
to shutting people out.

10:49.583 --> 10:52.166
If I had been open
to your offer of kindness,

10:52.166 --> 10:54.458
then you wouldn't have
needed to go to my home

10:54.875 --> 10:56.834
and you wouldn't have been attacked.

10:57.458 --> 10:59.125
Did you try the pie?

10:59.125 --> 11:01.792
The important thing is,

11:01.792 --> 11:05.417
if you still want to be friends,

11:05.417 --> 11:07.709
I suppose that would be okay,
Miss Newly.

11:09.083 --> 11:14.208
- That would be okay, what...?
- Samantha.

11:14.208 --> 11:15.375
[LAUGHS]

11:15.375 --> 11:16.875
- Yay!
- Oh, no, no.

11:16.875 --> 11:18.250
- Oh, yes.
- Get off of me. No.

11:18.250 --> 11:19.375
I'm gonna grab you till you--

11:20.083 --> 11:24.291
So Mr. Tony Dane
couldn't be bothered to show up, huh?

11:24.291 --> 11:26.959
Fine. Let's do this.

11:26.959 --> 11:29.041
First, I get to keep all the gifts.

11:29.041 --> 11:31.333
Second,
I still wanna go to the Grammy's.

11:31.792 --> 11:33.250
I was looking forward to that.

11:33.250 --> 11:35.041
And I don't care how you arrange it,

11:35.041 --> 11:37.000
but I wanna meet Tiger Woods,
James Gandolfini

11:37.000 --> 11:38.375
and Captain Jack Sparrow.

11:38.375 --> 11:40.792
- Are you finished?
- And I wanna carry the Olympic torch.

11:40.792 --> 11:44.166
- Okay, now.
- Here's our counteroffer.

11:46.000 --> 11:48.375
Andrea Belladonna,

11:48.709 --> 11:51.417
will you marry Tony Dane?

11:56.375 --> 11:59.291
Hey. Hey!
Where's your hideous red coat?

11:59.291 --> 12:01.583
If I have to wear the hideous red coat,
so do you.

12:01.583 --> 12:03.959
The showing has been canceled,
the sellers fired us.

12:03.959 --> 12:06.583
- What? Why?
- Remember the potential buyers?

12:06.583 --> 12:08.417
That couple you insulted?

12:08.417 --> 12:11.208
Well, they apparently own
the hottest new steakhouse in town

12:11.208 --> 12:14.083
and they're telling all their customers
that we are a racist company.

12:14.083 --> 12:16.333
- What?
- Oh, and two other clients have fired us.

12:16.333 --> 12:18.834
SAM: Okay, well, you know what?
You can't blame that on me.

12:18.834 --> 12:21.417
Because there could be a million reasons
why they fired us.

12:21.417 --> 12:24.458
First of all, you know,
we're not very good.

12:24.458 --> 12:27.583
You are gonna convince that couple
that you are not a racist.

12:27.583 --> 12:29.000
Unless, I don't know,

12:29.000 --> 12:31.417
- maybe you really are.
- Oh.

12:31.417 --> 12:34.291
When you were a baby, you cried
all the way through <i>The Jeffersons.</i>

12:34.291 --> 12:36.834
- Mom.
- And you don't have any black friends.

12:36.834 --> 12:39.875
Uh... Yes, I do. I have Frank.

12:39.875 --> 12:41.250
If they could see that then...

12:41.250 --> 12:42.667
[GASPS]

12:42.667 --> 12:44.333
FRANK:
This is a real nice steakhouse.

12:44.333 --> 12:46.750
- Thank you for inviting me.
- Yeah. Yeah, sure.

12:46.750 --> 12:49.583
You know, when you do real estate,
you don't just know about houses,

12:49.583 --> 12:51.875
you know about steakhouses,
you know?

12:51.875 --> 12:54.083
Oh, excuse me, miss. Hi.

12:54.083 --> 12:58.208
Can I please talk to the owners?
I don't like my steak, so...

12:58.208 --> 13:00.709
- I'm sorry, I can get you another one.
- No, I'll eat it.

13:00.709 --> 13:02.542
I just need to tell someone.

13:02.542 --> 13:06.083
- Okay, I'll get the chef.
SAM: Oh, no, no, no.

13:06.625 --> 13:09.500
- I need to talk to the owners.
- Okay, I'll see what I can do.

13:09.500 --> 13:10.709
Mm.

13:10.709 --> 13:13.417
- The skirt.
- All right, thanks.

13:13.417 --> 13:15.959
- This is fun, huh?
- It is.

13:15.959 --> 13:20.083
I'll admit as a rule, I try to avoid
being someone's first black friend.

13:20.083 --> 13:21.667
They try too hard.

13:21.667 --> 13:24.959
They start talking about Halle Berry,
how they voted for Obama,

13:24.959 --> 13:27.834
- how much they love Oprah.
- Yeah.

13:27.834 --> 13:29.000
Where are those owners?

13:29.000 --> 13:31.417
Hello, I understand someone
wanted to speak with the--

13:33.125 --> 13:36.250
- You.
- You own this place?

13:36.250 --> 13:37.458
I didn't know that.

13:37.458 --> 13:40.333
I love it. I love it.
So does my friend Frank here.

13:40.959 --> 13:42.458
- This is Frank.
- Oh.

13:43.375 --> 13:45.208
- Your friend, Frank.
- Yeah.

13:45.208 --> 13:48.625
So now I guess we can just stop
all the jibber-jabbering

13:48.625 --> 13:51.041
- about who my friends are, right?
- Oh, right.

13:51.041 --> 13:53.667
Because you thought
showing up with a black friend

13:53.667 --> 13:57.542
would stop us from reporting your racist
company to the real-estate board?

13:57.542 --> 14:00.208
- Pardon me?
SAM: Whoa, whoa, hey.

14:00.208 --> 14:03.208
Just because Frank here
might be black--

14:03.208 --> 14:05.458
I mean, is he? I don't know.
Are you black?

14:05.458 --> 14:08.250
Because I don't even see color at all.

14:08.250 --> 14:11.000
Does not mean
that he is not my actual friend.

14:11.000 --> 14:13.917
Okay? Please, Frank, tell her.

14:15.250 --> 14:17.208
Yes, ma'am.

14:17.208 --> 14:20.709
Why, Miss Samantha here,
she been real good to me.

14:20.709 --> 14:22.583
See, what I'm ta-- What?

14:22.583 --> 14:25.542
Oh, yes. Yes. You see lots of people,

14:25.542 --> 14:28.709
they don't take their doorman out
for no fancy meal.

14:28.709 --> 14:32.125
But Miss Samantha here,
she don't mind eating with the help.

14:32.875 --> 14:35.041
- He's your doorman?
- No.

14:35.542 --> 14:40.083
- He's not just my doorman.
- Oh, no. No, ma'am.

14:40.083 --> 14:43.417
Why, I also carry her things, to and fro.

14:43.417 --> 14:46.458
Why, she a real nice lady.

14:48.041 --> 14:50.959
You should be ashamed of yourself.

14:54.333 --> 14:57.500
First of all, dinner's on me.

14:57.959 --> 15:01.834
I-- Frank, come on.
Frank, please, come back.

15:01.834 --> 15:04.834
We pre-ordered the soufflé.

15:05.917 --> 15:08.291
So now Frank thinks
that I was using him

15:08.291 --> 15:11.083
just to prove that I had a black friend.

15:11.083 --> 15:13.709
- Which you were.
- No, I was not.

15:13.709 --> 15:17.709
I only used him after
we had already become friends, okay?

15:17.709 --> 15:21.250
And then, yes, I behaved very badly.

15:21.250 --> 15:23.417
You know,
I don't think he's a good influence on me.

15:23.417 --> 15:25.208
I might have to cut him out of my life.

15:25.208 --> 15:27.458
So you're not gonna even try
to be friends with him?

15:27.458 --> 15:29.041
I mean, what am I supposed to do?

15:29.041 --> 15:31.834
- Quitter.
- He doesn't want it.

15:31.834 --> 15:34.333
He hasn't even filed
a restraining order yet.

15:34.750 --> 15:36.667
I mean,
I waited 20 years to be your friend.

15:36.667 --> 15:39.291
You put up a fight,
but look where we are now.

15:39.291 --> 15:40.750
Yep, here we are.

15:40.750 --> 15:41.959
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

15:41.959 --> 15:45.291
I mean, you'd be amazed at the beautiful
friendships you can force on people.

15:46.208 --> 15:49.083
- Wow.
- So, what are you two losers

15:49.083 --> 15:50.333
doing in three months?

15:50.333 --> 15:52.875
[IN SINGSONG VOICE]
Because I'm getting married.

15:52.875 --> 15:55.583
- What? Oh, my God.
- Married to whom?

15:55.583 --> 15:56.917
[IN NORMAL VOICE]
To-- To who?

15:56.917 --> 15:58.542
Tony Dane, what do you think?

15:58.542 --> 16:01.792
- What do I think? I think he's gay.
- He's really gay, Andrea.

16:01.792 --> 16:06.166
And I think I've waited my entire life
to tell my friends that I'm engaged.

16:06.166 --> 16:09.250
So I think we should just put aside
the pesky details for one night

16:09.250 --> 16:11.250
and just get onboard, okay?

16:14.291 --> 16:16.417
[BOTH SHOUTING AND LAUGHING]

16:16.625 --> 16:18.750
Oh, my God, let me see that.
It is stunning.

16:18.750 --> 16:22.083
See, Tony's entering a contract here
and they don't want any bad press.

16:22.083 --> 16:23.834
So they're gonna
announce the engagement,

16:23.834 --> 16:27.291
and then all the designers are gonna bid
to see who's gonna make my dress,

16:27.291 --> 16:30.291
and the wedding photos
are already pre-sold to <i>People Magazine,</i>

16:30.291 --> 16:33.125
and they're paying Gwen Stefani
a hundred grand to show up

16:33.125 --> 16:34.917
and be my best friend.

16:34.917 --> 16:37.625
- It's like a fairy tale.
- I know.

16:37.625 --> 16:39.667
- I'll get us some champagne.
- Okay.

16:40.125 --> 16:43.000
See? She called me friend.
That didn't happen overnight.

16:43.000 --> 16:44.750
Yeah, well,
she's also marrying a gay dude

16:44.750 --> 16:46.792
so she might not be in her right mind.

16:46.792 --> 16:50.250
ANDREA:
Three champagnes. I'm engaged.

16:52.208 --> 16:54.250
What about the other night?

16:55.625 --> 16:59.000
Did you not just hear what I said?
I'm engaged.

16:59.000 --> 17:02.583
You felt something between us.
And I know you weren't that drunk.

17:02.583 --> 17:07.000
A little tip,
don't ever underestimate how drunk I am.

17:15.625 --> 17:17.291
You don't fool me.

17:17.291 --> 17:19.709
[DOORBELL BUZZING]

17:21.792 --> 17:23.500
[SIGHS]

17:24.625 --> 17:27.000
I think I know the answer to this.

17:27.000 --> 17:29.750
But do you care I have a little girl in here
who's trying to sleep?

17:29.750 --> 17:32.709
She'll be fine.
Marcello will take care of her.

17:33.083 --> 17:34.792
- If you came here to apologize--
- No.

17:35.250 --> 17:37.917
For wanting to be your friend? No.

17:37.917 --> 17:41.875
Am I perfect, Frank? No.
But we don't get to choose our friends.

17:41.875 --> 17:45.500
I mean, do you really think
that I chose Dena and Andrea?

17:45.500 --> 17:47.417
But there we are.

17:47.417 --> 17:49.375
- It's late, Miss Newly.
- Samantha.

17:49.375 --> 17:51.041
Miss Newly.

17:51.041 --> 17:53.417
We're going back
to the way things were before.

17:53.417 --> 17:56.166
- Before dinner?
- Before your accident.

17:56.166 --> 17:59.208
When you were as mean as a snake
and never gave me a glance.

17:59.709 --> 18:03.291
I didn't have to know you,
I didn't have to care about you.

18:03.291 --> 18:06.667
You said care. I heard it, Frank.
You said care.

18:07.166 --> 18:08.917
- Let's go, give me the money.
- What?

18:08.917 --> 18:10.208
SAM:
Oh, this is ridiculous.

18:10.208 --> 18:13.291
Seriously, guy, branch out.
Meet new people.

18:13.291 --> 18:15.125
Oh, damn.

18:15.125 --> 18:17.583
It's the chatty white lady
with no money in her purse.

18:17.583 --> 18:21.542
- Is this the man who mugged you?
- How can you have $5 and ten lipsticks?

18:21.542 --> 18:24.542
- You lied to the police.
- Maybe.

18:24.542 --> 18:27.583
But hey, you know what? If I had told them
who my real mugger was,

18:27.583 --> 18:30.417
- we wouldn't be sharing this right now.
- Yeah, I'm aware of that.

18:30.417 --> 18:32.875
Shared experiences, Frank, remember?

18:34.041 --> 18:35.792
Plus you care about me.

18:35.792 --> 18:39.959
You know what? If this guy shot me
right here and now, you would miss me.

18:39.959 --> 18:42.709
Hey, what? Hey. Who's got a gun?

18:42.709 --> 18:45.917
Not me. That's armed robbery,
a whole different thing.

18:45.917 --> 18:48.000
Just say it, Frank.

18:48.000 --> 18:50.291
I'll tell you what,
I'll close my eyes right now,

18:50.291 --> 18:51.792
you kidnap my friend,

18:52.458 --> 18:54.458
and if anybody asks,
I'll say it was a white guy.

18:54.458 --> 18:56.083
Why are you talking about
kidnapping?

18:56.083 --> 18:57.250
[CELL PHONE RINGS]

18:57.250 --> 18:58.625
Excuse me.

18:59.709 --> 19:02.417
Hello? Oh, it's the police.

19:04.083 --> 19:05.458
They found my mugger.

19:05.458 --> 19:09.000
Hey, forget this. I'd rather just get a job.

19:09.417 --> 19:11.250
Are you sure it's him?

19:11.250 --> 19:17.583
Because my description
was sort of vague and useless.

19:18.458 --> 19:23.041
So, ma'am, just tell us if the man
who robbed you is inside this room.

19:23.041 --> 19:24.709
Mm. Yeah, okay.

19:31.417 --> 19:32.875
[EXHALES]

19:34.125 --> 19:36.250
Wait a minute,
they can't really see me, right?

19:36.250 --> 19:37.917
- Why, do you see the guy?
- Right?

19:37.917 --> 19:42.083
Because we caught one of them
breaking into your car with your keys.

19:43.875 --> 19:46.542
Okay, Todd, seriously,
I am so sorry, all right?

19:46.542 --> 19:51.709
Look, I'll bet you soon, we'll tell this story
and we'll just laugh and laugh.

19:51.709 --> 19:54.125
- Yeah. What was your favorite part?
- Huh?

19:54.125 --> 19:57.667
- Mine was the delousing.
- Look, I'm sorry, okay?

19:57.667 --> 19:59.458
I had to come up with something quickly

19:59.458 --> 20:02.375
and I guess I just described
the first guy I thought of.

20:03.709 --> 20:05.250
Really?

20:05.667 --> 20:07.792
Yeah. What?

20:08.417 --> 20:12.542
- I was the first guy you thought of.
- Oh, don't get all cocky.

20:12.542 --> 20:14.375
Am I always the first guy you think of?

20:14.375 --> 20:16.583
Like in the morning, when you wake up?

20:16.583 --> 20:18.000
You know what? Shut up.

20:18.000 --> 20:21.583
It was probably just
that stupid little ratty mustache.

20:21.583 --> 20:23.583
I'll grow it some more
if you like it so much.

20:23.583 --> 20:26.125
Yeah, okay, you do that.
I'll see you in six months.

20:26.125 --> 20:27.583
You can't even look me in the eye.

20:28.000 --> 20:30.542
I should have had them put you away.

20:31.208 --> 20:35.041
Oh, that was almost
worth getting Tasered.

20:37.458 --> 20:40.000
SAM: <i>Okay, so anyway,</i>
<i>here's how to cure racism.</i>

20:40.000 --> 20:41.291
<i>And I want credit.</i>

20:41.291 --> 20:45.291
<i>If everyone on Earth just looks</i>
<i>into the eyes of every other person,</i>

20:45.291 --> 20:48.792
<i>we'll all be friends</i>
<i>and there will be no racism.</i>

20:49.208 --> 20:51.083
<i>Of course,</i>
<i>the logistics will be a nightmare</i>

20:51.083 --> 20:54.417
<i>and require exceptional</i>
<i>organizational skills.</i>

20:54.417 --> 20:56.583
<i>Maybe the Chinese can do it?</i>

20:56.583 --> 20:58.667
- Hey.
- Hey.

20:58.667 --> 21:02.041
- We're friends now, right?
- Yes. Absolutely.

21:02.041 --> 21:03.333
- Good.
- What?

21:03.333 --> 21:06.625
I need you to cover for me.
My band has a gig tonight.

21:07.291 --> 21:08.625
Oh.

21:12.000 --> 21:13.917
Can you call me a cab?

21:16.792 --> 21:18.875
[BLOWS WHISTLE]
